, New York|Mayor of Buffalo]]|years=1882}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marcus M. Drake]]}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Alonzo B. Cornell]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Governor of New York]]|years=1883\u20131885}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David B. Hill]]}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chester A. Arthur]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the United States|years=1885\u20131889}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Benjamin Harrison]]}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Benjamin Harrison]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the United States|years=1893\u20131897}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[William McKinley]]}}\n\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Lucius Robinson]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[New York gubernatorial elections|nominee]] for [[Governor of New York]]|years=[[1882 New York state election|1882]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[David B. Hill]]}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Winfield Scott Hancock]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] [[List of United States Democratic Party presidential tickets|nominee]] for President of the United States|years=[[1884 United States presidential election|1884]], [[1888 United States presidential election|1888]], [[1892 United States presidential election|1892]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[William Jennings Bryan]]}}\n\n{{s-hon}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Benjamin Harrison]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Oldest living President of the United States]]|years=1901\u20131908}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Theodore Roosevelt]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to Grover Cleveland\n|list1=\n{{US Presidents}}\n{{USDemPresNominees}}\n{{Unsuccessful major party pres candidates}}\n{{Governors of New York}}\n{{BuffaloMayors}}\n{{Cleveland 22 cabinet}}\n{{Cleveland 24 cabinet}}\n{{United States presidential election, 1884}}\n{{United States presidential election, 1888}}\n{{United States presidential election, 1892}}\n{{Hall of Fame for Great Americans}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Conservatism|New Jersey|New York (state)|Politics|Law|United States}}\n{{featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cleveland, Grover}}\n[[Category:Grover Cleveland| ]]\n[[Category:1837 births]]\n[[Category:1908 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:19th-century Presidents of the United States]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1884 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1888 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1892 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:American executioners]]\n[[Category:American lawyers admitted to the practice of law by reading law]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of German descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Guernsey descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scotch-Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American Presbyterians]]\n[[Category:Burials at Princeton Cemetery]]\n[[Category:Classical liberals]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party Presidents of the United States]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party (United States) presidential nominees]]\n[[Category:Governors of New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Grover Cleveland family]]\n[[Category:Hall of Fame for Great Americans inductees]]\n[[Category:History of the United States (1865\u20131918)]]\n[[Category:Lawyers from Buffalo, New York]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Buffalo, New York]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Democrats]]\n[[Category:New York (state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:Non-interventionism]]\n[[Category:People from Caldwell, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:People from Clinton, Oneida County, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Fayetteville, New York]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the United States]]\n[[Category:Sheriffs of Erie County, New York]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in New York (state)]]\n", "name_user": "Robert Pollard", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDefeated by Harrison:Cleland > Cleveland", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grover_Cleveland"}
{"title_page": "Adolf, Count Palatine of the Rhine", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=January 2009}}\n\n{{infobox noble\n| name        = Adolf\n| title       = [[List of rulers of the Electoral Palatinate|Count Palatine of the Rhine]]\n| image       = Wappen Kurfurst der Pfalz.png\n| image_size  = 150px\n| caption     = <small>Coat of arms of Count Palatine of Rhine</small>\n| reign       = 1319 \u2013 1327\n| predecessor = [[Rudolf I, Duke of Bavaria|Rudolf I]] (formally)\n| successor   = [[Louis IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Louis (IV)]]\n| noble family= [[House of Wittelsbach|Wittelsbach]]\n| father      = [[Rudolf I, Duke of Bavaria]]\n| mother      = [[Mechtild of Nassau]]\n| spouse      = [[Irmengard of Oettingen]]\n| issue       = [[Rupert II, Elector Palatine of the Rhine]]\n| issue-link = #Family and children\n| birth_date  = {{birth_date|1300|9|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Wolfratshausen]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1327|1|29|1300|7|27|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Neustadt]]\n| religion    = [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]]\n}}\n\n'''Adolf of the Rhine''' ({{lang-de|Adolf der Redliche von der Pfalz}}) (27 September 1300, [[Wolfratshausen]] \u2013 29 January 1327, [[Neustadt an der Weinstra\u00dfe|Neustadt]]) from the house of [[Wittelsbach]] was formally [[Count Palatine]] of the Rhine in 1319\u20131327.\n\nHe was the second son of [[Rudolf I, Duke of Bavaria]] and his wife [[Mechtild of Nassau]]. He didn't really rule because his uncle [[Louis IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Louis IV]] occupied the Palatinate until an [[Treaty of Pavia (1329)|agreement]] with Adolf's brothers and his son [[Rupert II, Elector Palatine of the Rhine]] was concluded in [[Pavia]] in 1329.\n\n==Family and children==\nHe was married in 1320 to Countess [[Irmengard of Oettingen]] (d. 1399), daughter of Count [[Louis VI of Oettingen]]. They had the following children:\n# [[Rupert II, Elector Palatine of the Rhine]] (12 May 1325, [[Amberg]]\u20136 January 1398, Amberg).\n# Adolf.\n# Friedrich.\n# a daughter (d. 1389), married Count Meinhard I of Ortenburg.\n\nHe was buried in the [[Cistercian]] monastery [[Sch\u00f6nau Abbey|Sch\u00f6nau]] near [[Heidelberg]].\n{{clear}}\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsible=yes\n|collapsed=yes\n|align=center\n|ref=\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1=1. '''Adolf'''\n|2=2. [[Rudolf I of Bavaria]]\n|3=3. [[Mechtild of Nassau]]\n|4=4. [[Louis II, Duke of Bavaria|Louis II of Bavaria]]\n|5=5. [[Matilda of Habsburg]]\n|6=6. [[Adolf of Germany]]\n|7=7. [[Imagina of Isenburg-Limburg]]\n|8=8. [[Otto II of Bavaria]]\n|9=9. [[Agnes of the Palatinate]]\n|10=10. [[Rudolf I of Germany]]\n|11=11. [[Gertrude of Hohenberg]]\n|12=12. [[Walram II of Nassau]]\n|13=13. Adelheid of Katzenelnbogen\n|14=14. [[Gerlach IV of Isenburg-Limburg]]\n|15=15. Imagina of Blieskastel\n|16=16. [[Louis I, Duke of Bavaria|Louis I of Bavaria]]\n|17=17. [[Ludmilla of Bohemia]]\n|18=18. [[Henry V of the Palatinate]]\n|19=19. [[Agnes of Hohenstaufen]]\n|20=20. [[Albert IV of Habsburg]]\n|21=21. Hedwig of Kyburg\n|22=22. Burkhard V of Hohenberg\n|23=23. Matilda of T\u00fcbingen\n|24=24. [[Henry II of Nassau]]\n|25=25. [[:nl:Machteld van Gelre|Matilda of Guelders]]\n|26=26. [[:de:Diether IV. (Katzenelnbogen)|Dieter IV of Katzenelnbogen]]\n|27=27. Hildegunde\n|28=28. Henry I of Isenburg-Grenzau\n|29=29. Irmingard of B\u00fcdingen\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|de}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20060621214858/http://www.genealogie-mittelalter.de/wittelsbacher_kurpfalz/adolf_kurfuerst_von_der_pfalz_1327.html www.genealogie-mittelalter.de]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-hou|[[House of Wittelsbach]]||1300||1327}}\n{{s-reg|}}\n{{succession box|\ntitle=[[Electoral Palatinate|(Titular) Elector Palatine of the Rhine]]|\nbefore=[[Rudolf I, Duke of Bavaria|Rudolf I]] (formally)|\